Installation can be done with 'configure+make' or with 'cmake'.

------------------------------------------------

Instalation with 'configure+make'

1) Get source tree
2) Run configuration:
  $ ./configure
3) compile the library
  $ make
4) That is all, you can use the library.
   Go to directory examples/ and check it.
   Good luck!

If you have some complex enevironement, try
  $ ./configure --help
and read options list.


------------------------------------------------

Instalation with 'cmake'

1. Get the source tree to some directory /..../ddd-source
2. Create a directory where you will build the library:
   Few examples:
   $ mkdir /..../ddd-source/build
   $ mkdir /tmp/build
3. Run CMake:
   $ cd <build-directory>
   $ cmake <path-to-ddd>
4. Compile it
   $ make
5. Create documentation (optional):
   $ make doc
6. Install it
   $ make install
